headline.main: W.E.B. DuBois Dies in Ghana; Negro Leader and Author, 95; Philosopher, Who Helped to Confound N.A.A.C.P., Later Turned to Communism Leader of Negro Thought At Fisk and Harvard Honored By Soviet

snippet: ACCRA, Ghana, Wednesday, Aug. 28--W.E.B. DuBois, the American Negro philosopher and writer, who settled in Ghana a few years ago, died last night, the Government announced. He was 95 years old.

byline.original: Special to The New York Times
